
[1]bet

   BET, n. A wager; that which is laid, staked or pledges in a contest, to
   be won, either by the victorious party himself, or by another person,
   in consequence of his victory. At a race, a man lays a bet on his own
   horse, or on the horse of another man.

   BET, v.t. To lay a bet; to lay a wager; to stake or pledge something
   upon the event of a context.

   BET, the old participle of beat, is obsolete or vulgar.
